review_blob:
Shouldnt it be "Amero-Belgian" or "Belgo-American"? American Belgo just seems wrong.

Anyway, cloudy gold color (sediment), nice head, strong clove-y aroma, along with some honey. Taste is BITTER. And sweet. Too bitter, IMO, out of balance. Also clove-y taste. 

Wanted to like it (9.99/4-pack). Didnt.

Nice Amarillo aroma (dry-hopped, probably), follows through in the taste. Some resin, as well. Not what I think of when I think "mild". Hoppy American mild, I guess. Light Copper color, big head, way overcarbed. Tastes great, but maybe American bitter would be closer to the style. Not malty--like sweet grapefruit & peach.
beer_name: Three Floyds Pride & Joy Mild Ale

review_blob: Slight aroma--cooked corn & rough hops (Cluster?). Taste is sweet corn, barely perceptible hops taste, no perceiveable bitterness. Looks good, except head dissipates rapidly. Overcarbonated, of course. Overall impression: yuck. Cmere, Rover, want some?

Huge white head which fades to 1/2". Aroma is sickly sweet malt with some unrecognizable grassy hops and soap. Taste is like hops candy--sickly sweet to start, very . very bitter finish. Kind of a metallic tang as well. Not my favorite, obvs. Mouthfeel is good if you can ignore the flavor.

Great beer. Hoppy and very light in color. Could use a bit more (light crystal) malt support. Aroma hops come through bright & clear--Ive read that El Dorado hops are in it, but tastes similar to Mosaic to me--maybe both.
Nice & malty with a substantial bitterness. A bit too clean for an English ESB--would like it a bit more estery. Almost more of a Scottish export. Good beer nonetheless.

Bottle-drink by 5/4/14. Nice deep copper color with a huge head. Crystal clear. Aroma of fruity hops--tangerines, apricots. Medium mouthfeel, slightly sweet, very balanced. Touch of fruity hops on the tongue as well. Nice bitterness, but not overdone. Hops hang around for a long finish.
